data.title: Feluga
data.text:
[WIP] Feluga, officially the Feluguese Republic (Feluguese: República Feluguesa), is a sovereign state located in the Amutian subcontinent of southern Europa. It is bordered by Qubdi to the west, Renolion to the east, and Red Iberos to the south. Sintra is the capital and largest city by population.

Feluga is one of the oldest continuously existing nation state on the Amutian subcontinent, its territory having been continuously settled, invaded and fought over since prehistoric times. It was inhabited by pre-Geltic and Geltic peoples who had contact with Laimiaic traders, it was ruled by the Aroman, followed by the invasions of Qubdi who eventually were expelled.

In the 16th and 17th centuries, Feluga experienced a dark period during the Gran Viatge. This period has been recognised as the Baltasar Regime, when most of the Feluguese lower-middle strata people were brutally murdered.

By the early of 17th century, voyagers and traders from the north-west known from Goutian East Trade Company (Gotaish: Goutian Verslunarfélag Austurs) have arrived in Portalegre. As Baltasar isolationist foreign policy, the Goutian East Trade Company were not warmly welcomed and Fionn, who led the expedition, was taken into custody by Baltasar's men.

Feluguese' economy is driven by ($MainEconomy). Feluga is part of several international and intergovernmental institutions, including the Assembled Nations.

Etymology

The word Feluga derives from the Aroman-Geltic place name Veloca; a city where present-day Veloz and Morisca. The Aroman took over the basecamp of the Velones and named it to Veloca to simplify Velones Loca (literally means the Velones’ dwelling place).

Birth of Tribonditas and the Republic

1979: Emperor Patrick XIII of the Goutian Empire transferred full authority and recognition of the sovereignty of the State.

1979-1988: Emerging of Communism from Red Iberos.

30 September 1988: Movimento Frente Azul (MFA) to eradicate Communism.

5 October 1988: Birth of Tribonditas and the Republic.

25 March 1990: Constitution of the Republic.
